The paper discusses the ability of deep neural networks to solve computationally hard problems, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also explores the bias in data generation techniques, which is relevant to data science (cs.DS). The specific case study mentioned, Conjunctive Query Containment, falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and cryptography (cs.CR).
